ALMA
====

Instructions
------------

, ind
; ind!
. ws
: ws!
! nl!

_ any
' many
` one

# doxy
* do
+ do!
? do?
1 do1
2 do2
3 do3
4 do4
5 do5
6 do6
7 do7
8 do8
9 do9

@ ref
= rec
	
( nest
) ret
[ case
| brk
] end

~ fill
< lock
> head

Syntactic Sugar
---------------
␣...?␣       ⇢ (?...)
␣...*␣       ⇢ (*...)
␣...+␣       ⇢ (+...)
␣...*n-m␣    ⇢ (#nm...)
␣...5␣       ⇢ (5...)
␣...5+␣      ⇢ (5+...)
␣(...)?␣     ⇢ (?...)
␣[...]*␣     ⇢ (*...)

name␣=␣...\n ⇢  (=name...)
name␣=␣(...) ⇢ ␣(=name...)
name␣=␣[...] ⇢ ␣[=name...] 

(␣  = any white-space)

Files
-----

alma/
+-- _data/        example input files parsed in tests
+-- alma/         several grammars specified in alma language
+-- java/         java implementation

